OL,6,FGuernsey politicians had agreed to the
OL,7,Fcurrent proposals - including
OL,8,Fextending the runway to allow larger
OL,9,Fplanes to land - in December 2022.
OL,11,FMore than 600 flights to and from
OL,12,FAlderney were delayed or cancelled due
OL,13,Fto adverse weather conditions in 2023,
OL,14,Faccording to a Freedom of Information
OL,15,Fresponse from the States of Guernsey.
OL,17,FAll commercial flights to and from
OL,18,FAlderney are currently operated by the
OL,19,Fairline Aurigny which uses 19-seater
OL,20,Fplanes to fly to the island.
